Vice President Mike Pence spoke at an event in Santiago, Chile celebrating 50 years of the Association of American Chambers of Commerce in Latin America and 100 years of the American Chamber in Chile. He emphasized the importance of a strong economic partnership between the United States and Latin America, and expressed the Trump administration's commitment to trade and investment in the region. Pence also discussed the need for market-based reforms, reduced taxation, and decreased regulation to stimulate economic growth. He highlighted the success of the U.S.-Chile Free Trade Agreement and called for compliance with intellectual property rights. Pence also addressed the crisis in Venezuela, expressing support for the Venezuelan people and pledging to work with Latin American allies to restore democracy in the country. He concluded by emphasizing the importance of freedom and the shared values that unite the countries of the Western Hemisphere.